                            <comment id="16598983" author="shenyufeng" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2018 16:38:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After doing some checking I found Flink stop its components(JM&amp;amp;&amp;amp;TM) by reading the pid file firstly then run cmd kill pid, and Till Rohrmann mentioned by default the pid file is written to&#160;/tmp&#160;and has the name&#160;flink-&amp;lt;USER&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;FLINK_COMPONENT&amp;gt;.pid and can control the dir by setting the&#160;env.pid.dir&#160;configuration in&#160;flink-conf.yaml to avoid this issue temporarily.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So by default should the Flink use the&#160; flink-&amp;lt;USER&amp;gt;&amp;lt;&lt;b&gt;CLUSERID&lt;/b&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;FLINK_COMPONENT&amp;gt;.pid instead? And also the non-public config item env.pid.dir&#160; should be published in the official document.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
